@c ============================================================================
@node Introduction
@chapter Introduction

@cindex folgezettel
@cindex Zettelkasten
@cindex Luhmann

Autoslip Roam is an Emacs package that brings Niklas Luhmann's
folgezettel (follow-up slip) system to org-roam.  The package automatically
manages bidirectional links between parent and child notes based on their
folgezettel addresses.

@section What is a Folgezettel?

A folgezettel is a sequential numbering system used in the Zettelkasten
(slip-box) method.  Each note has an address that encodes its position in
a hierarchy of ideas.  For example:

@itemize @bullet
@item
@code{1.} - A root note (first topic); the trailing period is the canonical marker for a root
@item
@code{1.2} - Second subtopic of note 1
@item
@code{1.2a} - First branch from 1.2
@item
@code{1.2a3} - Third continuation of 1.2a
@end itemize

Legacy titles without the trailing period on the root (e.g., @code{1 Crystallography}) are still recognized and treated as equivalent to the canonical @code{1.} form.

@section Features

@itemize @bullet
@item
Automatic parent backlink generation when creating child notes
@item
Automatic forward link insertion in parent notes
@item
Bidirectional cross-linking when manually inserting links
@item
Validation to prevent invalid addresses
@item
Duplicate index detection
@item
Suggestions for next child address
@item
Database synchronization for immediate link visibility
@item
Navigation commands to jump to the parent, list direct children, or show
the whole vault as a folgezettel-ordered tree
@item
Reparent commands that move a note (or an entire subtree) to a new
folgezettel address and keep titles, links, and filenames in sync
@item
Chain-of-thought commands that render the path from a note to its root
in a dedicated buffer and can insert that path into the current note
@item
Cross-linked chain-of-thought command that shows the folgezettel
context of every note linked under Cross References
@item
Optional property-drawer link-storage mode for a quieter note body
@end itemize

@c ============================================================================
@node Installation
@chapter Installation

@section Requirements

@itemize @bullet
@item
Emacs 27.1 or later
@item
org-roam 2.0 or later
@end itemize

@section From MELPA

@findex package-install
Once the package is available on MELPA:

@example
M-x package-install RET autoslip-roam RET
@end example

@section Manual Installation

@enumerate
@item
Clone the repository:
@example
git clone https://github.com/MooersLab/autoslip-roam.git
@end example

@item
Add to your load path in @file{init.el}:
@lisp
(add-to-list 'load-path "/path/to/autoslip-roam")
(require 'autoslip-roam)
@end lisp

@item
Enable the mode:
@lisp
(autoslip-roam-mode 1)
@end lisp
@end enumerate

@section Installing the Info Manual

To install the Info manual for access within Emacs:

@example
make info
sudo make install-info
@end example

Or manually:

@example
makeinfo autoslip-roam.texi
sudo cp autoslip-roam.info /usr/local/share/info/
sudo install-info /usr/local/share/info/autoslip-roam.info \
    /usr/local/share/info/dir
@end example

Then access via @kbd{C-h i d m Autoslip Roam RET}.

@c ============================================================================
@node Quick Start
@chapter Quick Start

@section Basic Setup

Add to your @file{init.el}:

@lisp
(require 'autoslip-roam)
(autoslip-roam-mode 1)
@end lisp

@section Creating Your First Notes

@enumerate
@item
Create a root note with a folgezettel title:
@example
M-x org-roam-node-find RET
Title: 1. My First Topic
@end example

@item
Open the root note and create a child:
@example
M-x autoslip-roam-insert-next-child RET
@end example

@item
The package suggests @code{1.1} as the first child.  Enter a title when prompted.

@item
Both notes now have bidirectional links:
@itemize @minus
@item
Child note has ``Parent Note'' section with link to @code{1.}
@item
Parent note has ``Child Notes'' section with link to child
@end itemize
@end enumerate

@c ============================================================================
@node Folgezettel Addresses
@chapter Folgezettel Addresses

@cindex address format
@cindex hierarchy

@section Address Structure

Folgezettel addresses follow a strict hierarchical pattern:

@table @code
@item 1., 2., 3., ...
Root notes (a number followed by a trailing period); bare-integer legacy forms are accepted
@item 1.1, 1.2, 1.13, ...
First-level subtopics (number DOT number)
@item 1.2a, 1.2b, ..., 1.2z
Letter branches (lowercase letters)
@item 1.2aa, 1.2ab, ..., 1.2zz
Extended letter branches (after z comes aa)
@item 1.2a1, 1.2a2, ...
Numeric continuations of letter branches
@end table

@section Alternation Rules

The address system follows strict alternation:

@enumerate
@item
Root numbers can only have DOT-number children (@code{1.} @result{} @code{1.1})
@item
DOT-number nodes can only have letter children (@code{1.1} @result{} @code{1.1a})
@item
Letter-ending nodes can only have number children (@code{1.1a} @result{} @code{1.1a1})
@item
The pattern continues alternating
@end enumerate

@section Parent-Child Relationships

@multitable @columnfractions .3 .3 .4
@headitem Child @tab Parent @tab Relationship
@item @code{1.2} @tab @code{1.} @tab Remove .number, leave root period
@item @code{1.2a} @tab @code{1.2} @tab Remove letters
@item @code{1.2aa} @tab @code{1.2} @tab Remove ALL letters
@item @code{1.2a3} @tab @code{1.2a} @tab Remove trailing number
@item @code{1.2a3b} @tab @code{1.2a3} @tab Remove trailing letters
@end multitable

@section Valid vs Invalid Addresses

@subsection Valid Examples
@itemize @bullet
@item @code{1.} - Root note (canonical); @code{1} is also accepted as a legacy bare form
@item @code{1.13} - Multi-digit subtopic
@item @code{1.2a} - Single letter branch
@item @code{1.2aa} - Extended letter (27th child)
@item @code{1.2a3c5d7} - Deep hierarchy
@end itemize

@subsection Invalid Examples
@itemize @bullet
@item @code{1.2.3} - Multiple periods not allowed
@item @code{1.2A} - Uppercase not allowed
@item @code{1.2a!} - Special characters not allowed
@item @code{a1} - Must start with number
@end itemize

@c ============================================================================
@node Usage
@chapter Usage

@section Automatic Link Creation

@cindex automatic linking
When @code{autoslip-roam-mode} is enabled, creating a new note with
a folgezettel address automatically:

@enumerate
@item
Identifies the parent note based on the address
@item
Inserts a backlink under @samp{** Parent Note} in the new note
@item
Inserts a forward link under @samp{** Child Notes} in the parent
@end enumerate

@section Creating Child Notes

@findex autoslip-roam-insert-next-child
The recommended way to create child notes:

@example
M-x autoslip-roam-insert-next-child
@end example

This command:
@enumerate
@item
Reads the current note's folgezettel address
@item
Suggests the next available child address
@item
Prompts for a title
@item
Creates the note with proper bidirectional links
@end enumerate

@section Manual Link Addition

@findex autoslip-roam-add-backlink-to-parent
For existing notes without links:

@example
M-x autoslip-roam-add-backlink-to-parent
@end example

@section Cross-Reference Links

@cindex cross-references
When you insert a link to another org-roam note using @kbd{C-c C-l} or
@code{org-roam-node-insert}, a reciprocal link is automatically created
in the target note under @samp{** Cross References}.

This can be disabled:
@lisp
(setq autoslip-roam-auto-crosslink nil)
@end lisp

@c ============================================================================
@node Customization
@chapter Customization

@findex customize-group
All customization options are in the @code{autoslip-roam} group:

@example
M-x customize-group RET autoslip-roam RET
@end example

@section Link Descriptions

@defopt autoslip-roam-parent-link-description
Description text for parent links.  Default: @code{"Parent note"}.
@end defopt

@defopt autoslip-roam-child-link-description
Description for child links.  If @code{nil} (default), uses the child's title.
@end defopt

@section Headings

@defopt autoslip-roam-backlink-heading
Heading for parent links in child notes.  Default: @code{"Parent Note"}.
Set to @code{nil} to insert without a heading.
@end defopt

@defopt autoslip-roam-forward-link-heading
Heading for child links in parent notes.  Default: @code{"Child Notes"}.
@end defopt

@defopt autoslip-roam-crosslink-heading
Heading for cross-reference links.  Default: @code{"Cross References"}.
@end defopt

@section Behavior

@defopt autoslip-roam-auto-crosslink
Enable automatic reciprocal links when inserting cross-references.
Default: @code{t}.
@end defopt

@defopt autoslip-roam-sync-db-before-queries
Sync org-roam database before queries.  Default: @code{t}.
Recommended for reliability.
@end defopt

@section Link Storage

@defopt autoslip-roam-link-storage
How to record parent and child references.  The value @code{'headings}
(default) writes visible @samp{** Parent Note} and @samp{** Child Notes}
sections in the note body.  The value @code{'properties} writes the
references to a top-level property drawer instead, keeping the body
untouched.  The property-drawer mode is useful in shared vaults where
the visible heading noise creates merge-conflict surface.
@end defopt

@defopt autoslip-roam-parent-property
Property key used for the parent reference when link storage is
@code{'properties}.  Default: @code{"FZ_PARENT"}.
@end defopt

@defopt autoslip-roam-children-property
Property key used for the list of child references when link storage is
@code{'properties}.  Default: @code{"FZ_CHILDREN"}.
@end defopt

@section Reparenting

@defopt autoslip-roam-rename-files-on-reparent
Whether @code{autoslip-roam-reparent} and
@code{autoslip-roam-reparent-subtree} should rename each affected
file on disk so that the filename prefix matches the new folgezettel
address.  Default: @code{t}.
@end defopt

@section Chain of Thought

@defopt autoslip-roam-chain-heading
Second-level heading written above a chain-of-thought outline that is
inserted into a note.  Default: @code{"Chain of Thought"}.  Set to
@code{nil} to insert without a heading.
@end defopt

@defopt autoslip-roam-chain-crosslink-heading
Heading written above cross-linked chains-of-thought inserted into a
note.  Default: @code{"Cross-linked Chains of Thought"}.
@end defopt

@section Example Configuration

@lisp
(use-package autoslip-roam
  :after org-roam
  :config
  (setq autoslip-roam-parent-link-description "↑ Parent"
        autoslip-roam-backlink-heading "Parent Note"
        autoslip-roam-forward-link-heading "Child Notes"
        autoslip-roam-auto-crosslink t)
  (autoslip-roam-mode 1))
@end lisp

@c ============================================================================
@node Commands
@chapter Commands

@section Interactive Commands

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-mode
Toggle the minor mode.  When enabled, automatically creates bidirectional
links for new notes with folgezettel addresses.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-insert-next-child
Create a new child note of the current note.  Suggests the next available
address and prompts for a title.  Creates bidirectional links automatically.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-add-backlink-to-parent
Manually add bidirectional links between the current note and its parent.
Useful for existing notes or when automatic linking fails.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-report-validation-errors address
Interactively validate an address and display any errors.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-diagnose-address address
Diagnose issues finding a folgezettel address in the database.
Shows all nodes and their extracted addresses.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-check-duplicate-index address
Check if an address is already used.  Warns if duplicate found.
@end deffn

@section Navigation Commands

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-goto-parent
Visit the parent of the current note.  The parent is the node whose
folgezettel address is one step shallower than the current one.  Errors
when the current note is a root.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-list-children
Prompt with a completion list of the current note's direct children,
ordered by folgezettel, and visit the selection.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-show-tree
Open the @file{*Autoslip Tree*} buffer, a read-only outline of every
folgezettel-addressed node in the vault, sorted in canonical folgezettel
order and indented by depth.  In that buffer, @kbd{RET} visits the node on
the current line, @kbd{n} and @kbd{p} move between lines, @kbd{g} refreshes
the view, and @kbd{q} buries the buffer.
@end deffn

@section Chain-of-Thought Commands

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-show-chain-of-thought
Open the @file{*Autoslip Chain of Thought*} buffer, which lists every
ancestor of the current note from root to leaf along a single folgezettel
chain.  The view shows only the connecting notes (not the rest of the
subtree).  In that buffer, @kbd{RET} visits the node on the current line,
@kbd{i} inserts the chain into the note that opened the buffer, @kbd{g}
refreshes, @kbd{n} and @kbd{p} move between lines, and @kbd{q} buries the
buffer.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-insert-chain-of-thought
Insert the current note's chain of thought at point as an indented org
bullet list.  Each bullet is a link to the corresponding org-roam node,
and the heading above the list is controlled by
@code{autoslip-roam-chain-heading}.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-show-crosslinked-chains
Open the @file{*Autoslip Cross-linked Chains*} buffer.  For every note
linked under @code{autoslip-roam-crosslink-heading} in the current
note, the command walks that note's own folgezettel chain and renders it
as a distinct block in the buffer.  This gives the reader the context each
cross-link sits in rather than just the link's title.  Press @kbd{i} in
the buffer to insert all the chains into the current note.
@end deffn

@section Reparenting Commands

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-reparent new-address
Change the folgezettel address of the current note to
@var{new-address}.  The command validates the new address, rejects
duplicates, updates the title keyword, rewrites the parent backlink, and
updates the old and new parents' forward-link sections.  When
@code{autoslip-roam-rename-files-on-reparent} is non-nil, it also
renames the file on disk.
@end deffn

@deffn Command autoslip-roam-reparent-subtree new-address
Like @code{autoslip-roam-reparent}, but also moves every descendant
of the current note so that their addresses all shift to live under
@var{new-address}.  The command pre-checks for address collisions with
unrelated notes and aborts without making changes if any are found.
@end deffn

@section Suggested Key Bindings

@lisp
(with-eval-after-load 'org-roam
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n c") #'autoslip-roam-insert-next-child)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n p") #'autoslip-roam-add-backlink-to-parent)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n u") #'autoslip-roam-goto-parent)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n d") #'autoslip-roam-list-children)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n t") #'autoslip-roam-show-tree)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n h") #'autoslip-roam-show-chain-of-thought)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n H") #'autoslip-roam-insert-chain-of-thought)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n x") #'autoslip-roam-show-crosslinked-chains)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n r") #'autoslip-roam-reparent)
  (define-key org-mode-map (kbd "C-c n R") #'autoslip-roam-reparent-subtree))
@end lisp

